<p>A lot of times you will hear people say that you lose hair because it&#8217;s totally hereditary and can&#8217;t be stopped. They say it&#8217;s in your genes. Well really this is only partly true. There are things that have to do with our genetics that can cause us to lose hair, but it&#8217;s not the determining factor.</p>
<p>You see most of us lose our hair because of having a high level of DHT within our bodies. DHT is a hormone that leads to hair loss by binding to hair follicle receptor cells. When in high levels, it literally starts to make your hair thinner and thinner.</p>
<p>You can easily stop this by taking various herbs that actually naturally block DHT. One popular one is saw palmetto extract. Taking this herb daily like you would any other vitamin or mineral supplement will certainly keep DHT at bay.</p>
